{
  "texts": [
    "We conducted semi-structured interviews among 37 regular Facebook users to address and investigate these questions.",
    "We asked the participants questions about their usage patterns, their opinions regarding the need to explain recommended content, and how explanations could impact their social media use.",
    "Analysis of the interview data shows that the answers to RQ1 discuss that users require explanation for recommendations due to (i) content recommendation opacity, (ii) the lack of clarity regarding users' personal data usage, and (iii) lack of logical reasoning over technical explanation.",
    "The concern about content recommendation opacity illustrates that users want to be informed about how the recommendations are made.",
    "Users often need clarification if they come across unfamiliar recommendations."
  ]
}